accessibility.text: A rightward shift in the Supply of funds
A purchase of bonds by the Fed floods the banking system with additional reserves
Assume the market starts at equilibrium
When the Fed buys bonds: Quantitative Easing (QE)
The Supply of funds in this market increase
There will be more banks with excess Reserves
